Usage:  p7verify -c content -s signature [-d dbdir] [-u certusage]
-c content           content file that was signed
-s signature         file containing signature for that content
-d dbdir             Key/Cert database directory (default is ~/.netscape)
-u certusage         Define the type of certificate usage (default is certUsageEmailSigner)
                           0 - certUsageSSLClient
                           1 - certUsageSSLServer
                           2 - certUsageSSLServerWithStepUp
                           3 - certUsageSSLCA
                           4 - certUsageEmailSigner
                           5 - certUsageEmailRecipient
                           6 - certUsageObjectSigner
                           7 - certUsageUserCertImport
                           8 - certUsageVerifyCA
                           9 - certUsageProtectedObjectSigner
                          10 - certUsageStatusResponder
                          11 - certUsageAnyCA
                          12 - certUsageIPsec
